The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, July 4: Telecom minister A. Raja today met Prime Minister Manmohan Singh and briefed him on the proposed policy on third generation (3G) mobile services and WiMax. The policy is likely to be announced next week. Sources said Raja apprised the Prime Minister of the 3G spectrum auction process and the modalities associated with it.                            
	 Mumbai, July 4: The Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) today clarified central and state government employees would have to quote permanent account numbers (PAN) for all stock market transactions undertaken by them in personal capacity.                            
	 New Delhi/ Madrid, July 4: ONGC Videsh Ltd, the overseas arm of state-run Oil and Natural Gas Corporation, has been shortlisted to qualify as an operator for the deep water blocks by Angola.                             
	 Mumbai, July 4: Cadila Healthcares board has approved the restructuring of its consumer products division as a subsidiary firm under Carnation Nutra-Analogue Foods for an agreed share swap ratio of 4:15.                            
	 Sydney, July 4: BHP Billiton Ltd said Chinas Baosteel, negotiating on behalf of the Chinese steel industry, agreed to price hikes of up to 96.5 per cent for ore supply.                                                                                                                         
